  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "When I'm authoring or editing a message, I'm able to use the UP and DOWN arrow keys on my keyboard to move to the previous or the next line in the word-wrapped text. When I'm already at the top-most line (but in the middle of it), I expect that pressing the UP arrow again will position my cursor at the beginning of the message (thus, pressing UP multiple times in succession is a convenient way to simulate the behavior of the HOME button on keyboards lacking a dedicated HOME button). The same is true for the DOWN arrow which can be used to produce the effect of a dedicated END button.\r\n\r\nThis convenient behavior is currently not present in Status Desktop (version 0.8 on macOS)\r\n",
